This is the dramatic moment a mother was pulled to safety by rescuers after she got stuck in a mud trap while out with her two young sons.

The family of three, thought to be from Manchester, were enjoying a holiday in Conwy, North Wales, when they got into difficulty on the seafront.

Onlookers saw the mother, in her 30s, and her two boys, aged eight and ten, begin sinking into the mud, before they were spotted by a member of a nearby lifeboat crew as the sludge rose to their waists.

