RNLI crew members then triggered a rescue mission and hauled the family to safety through the mud and back on to dry land on Conwy Quay.

'On Saturday at 6.23pm we got a call to a family who had become stuck in the mud on Conwy Quay,' said a spokesman from Conwy RNLI.

'The family from the Manchester area were spotted by one of the lifeboat crew who was passing at the time.

