'The inshore lifeboat was not launched to this incident and the crew proceeded on foot.'

One crew member waded out into the mud and tossed an orange lifebelt to the stranded trio before carrying them to safety.

The spokesman added: 'The three casualties were quickly extracted and taken ashore. They were muddy but otherwise none the worse for their ordeal.

'The crew returned to the lifeboat station at 6.50pm and, after a good hosing down, were ready for immediate response.'

